{"id":"ev_11d2d3b7a16f410e","runId":"run_248","type":"delegation","at":1782488165088,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_554e271fd68e47a1","atom":1,"task":"Ticket 0064 — Atom 2 (final required item): add the regression repro the ticket mandates — a PROCESS-LEVEL test proving the real daemon actually EXITS on shutdown even with a dashboard stream open, so it can never linger as the zombie from the 2026-06-25 incident.\n\nWhy this is needed even though component tests exist: atom 0 already added `tests/server-close.test.ts` (close() resolves with an open SSE client), `tests/events.test.ts` (shutdown closes streams), and `tests/oz-script.test.ts` (SOURCE assertions that bin/oz.mjs has the SIGKILL watchdog + idempotent guard, and oz.sh reaps by pattern). What NONE of them do is spawn the REAL `packages/daemon/bin/oz.mjs` process and prove the actual SIGTERM→exit path works end-to-end. The incident was a real process that would not die; only a real-process test proves the fix.\n\nAdd a new test file `packages/daemon/tests/daemon-exit-repro.test.ts` that:\n1. Spawns the real daemon binary: `node packages/daemon/bin/oz.mjs --port <freePort>` with `cwd` set to a fresh temp install fixture. Reuse `writeInstallFixture(home, ['cocoder'])` from `tests/helpers/daemon-reload-fixture.ts` to lay down a valid cocoderHome (it creates the `local/` layout the daemon boots against). Pick a concrete free port (e.g. bind a throwaway `net` server to :0, read the assigned port, close it, reuse that number) — do not use 0 for the spawned bin since the test must reach it by URL.\n2. Waits for the daemon to be up by polling `GET http://127.0.0.1:<port>/health` with a BOUNDED deadline (e.g. up to 10s, then fail with a clear message — never an unbounded/infinite poll). If it cannot come up in the sandbox, fail loudly rather than hang.\n3. Opens a real SSE stream to `/oz/events` (Bearer from `GET /auth/session`, mirroring the `openSse` helper pattern in `tests/server-close.test.ts`/`tests/events.test.ts`) and confirms it received `: connected`/a frame — i.e. a live dashboard-style stream is genuinely held open.\n4. Sends `SIGTERM` to the child and asserts the child process EMITS its `exit` event within a bounded window (e.g. <= 5000ms — the bin's force-exit watchdog is 2500ms). This is the core repro: an open stream must NOT keep the old process alive. Assert it exited (exit/close event fired); the exit code may be 0 (clean) or the watchdog code — accept either, the point is that it died.\n5. After exit, prove no zombie holds the port: assert that a fresh `net` server can immediately bind the same port (i.e. the port is free / nothing survives on it). This is the test-faithful stand-in for the ticket's 'no surviving oz.mjs besides the new listener'.\n6. TEARDOWN MUST BE BULLETPROOF: in `afterEach`/`finally`, if the child is still alive, `child.kill('SIGKILL')` it (and best-effort reap any stray), and `rm` the temp home. The test must never leak a real running daemon on the dev machine. Give the test a generous per-test timeout (e.g. 20000ms) so a slow boot doesn't flake as a false failure.\n\nNotes / constraints:\n- The bin boots with `warmCliCacheOnBoot:true`, which fires background CLI probes; that is fine — tolerate it, do NOT edit the bin to disable it (out of scope). Just ensure teardown kills the child so nothing lingers.\n- Do NOT modify `bin/oz.mjs`, `server.ts`, `oz.sh`, or any non-test source — this atom is test-only.\n- Match the existing test style (vitest, the fixture helpers, the `openSse`/`waitFor`/`withTimeout` helper shapes already in `tests/server-close.test.ts`).\n\nWrite-scope (test-only): `packages/daemon/tests/**`.\n\nMust not break: the full daemon suite stays green; the new test is deterministic within its bounded deadlines (no infinite polls, guaranteed child teardown).\n\nExit criterion (run and paste output): `pnpm --filter @cocoder/daemon test` is green INCLUDING the new `daemon-exit-repro` test, and `pnpm --filter @cocoder/core --filter @cocoder/daemon typecheck` passes. In your summary, paste the spawn→SIGTERM→exit timing the test observed (proving the real process died within the watchdog window)."}}
